$grp PS_MissionDescription : "{3136BE42592F3B1B}PrefabsEditable/MissionDescription/EditableMissionDescription.et" {
 brief_overview {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Overview"
  m_sTextData "Delta Force assaults a castle in order to prevent the detonation of a low yield nuclear device."\
  ""\
  "Loose remake of goosko's Arma 3 Countdown mission."\
  ""\
  "NOTE FOR GAME MASTERS:"\
  "There are a couple civilian \"resident\" slots marked as \"slot last\" - these should NOT be filled according to ratio, only when there are no other slots left - lock these unless there are enough players."\
  "The civilian \"hostage\" slots can be filled normally according to ratio."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
 }
 brief_notes {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Notes"
  m_sTextData "5 minute setup timer, affecting the US main force."\
  "US recon team can move immediately."\
  ""\
  "Default start time is dusk, about 10 minutes before darkness starts setting in or 20 minutes before full darkness. Weather is random."\
  ""\
  "The hidden castle entrance marked on the map leads through a tunnel, up some stairs, into the southern courtyard."\
  ""\
  "End conditions:"\
  "- US victory if the bomb is disarmed"\
  "- US defeat if the bomb explodes after 35 minutes, or at 90% casualties"\
  ""\
  "At the moment, GMs must disable global supply usage so the mortar has ammunition."
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 brief_hostages {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Hostage Briefing"
  m_sTextData "You are a civilian (e. g. tourist, worker, local) who was at Pasastejn castle when a group of armed men showed up."\
  ""\
  "You don't know much else about what is going on, but they appear to a violent extremist group, possibly terrorists, from a neighboring country that has historically been involved in ethnic conflicts with Bystrany."\
  ""\
  "They have taken you hostage and threatened to kill you, if you should attempt to flee."\
  ""\
  "You are afraid for your life, and the armed men do not seem tolerant towards acts of bravery or resistance - so your plan is to just to..."\
  "- comply with basic orders,"\
  "- not attempt to flee on your own accord,"\
  "- do your best to not provoke them,"\
  "- and hope everything will turn out fine."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "CIV"
  }
 }
 brief_residents {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Resident Briefing"
  m_sTextData "You are a resident living in the village of Pasastejn."\
  "You were having a normal day, until a couple of hours ago, you heard gunfire coming from the local castle."\
  ""\
  "You don't know any hard facts, but there are rumors going through the village that a group of foreign armed men arrived at the castle, and started threatening people."\
  ""\
  "You are curious what is going on, but also a little anxious and do not feel like risking anything."\
  ""\
  "You definitely want to keep some distance to the castle, but perhaps you can explore the local area and see if you can find out more, e. g. by observing it from a distance."\
  ""\
  ""\
  ""\
  "Note: If you open your inventory when you spawn, you will see there are some flashlights you can pick up."
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "CIV"
  }
  m_iOrder 2
 }
 brief_us {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Briefing"
  m_sTextData "<h1>SITUATION</h1>"\
  "A couple of hours ago, an armed extremist group (from a neighboring country of Bystrany) took control of Pasastejn castle."\
  "The group is known for its deep ethnic hatred of Bystranian nationals, and according to preliminary intel, is in posession of a low yield nuclear device that they plan to detonate, destroying the historic castle and killing thousands of Bystranian civilians."\
  "Current intelligence suggests the nuclear device is still being armed, but might be ready for detonation around T+35m."\
  "Since Bystrany is a close ally of the United States, 1st SFOD-D has scrambled to assemble a task force which will attempt to neutralize the threat."\
  ""\
  "<b>a. Enemy Forces</b>"\
  "10-15 men, largely using Soviet style small arms. They likely have only very limited night vision capabilities."\
  "Most terrorists are likely within the castle, but some may also be in the surrounding area, marked in orange."\
  ""\
  "<b>b. Friendly Forces</b>"\
  "2 assault teams and 1 support team, standing by for aerial insertion from Bysovice Airfield."\
  "A recon team has already been quietly inserted at the chosen location (marked TP points), and is e. g. able to secure an LZ within the enemies AO or establish early observation on the castle."\
  ""\
  "<b>c. Other</b>"\
  "There is civilian presence in the village of Pasastejn."\
  "The terrorists have also reportedly taken a couple of hostages, which they might try to use as civilian shields."\
  "Caution is advised when considering engagement of unidentified targets - while the mission might take priority under extreme circumstances, the chance of harm to civilians should be avoided whenever feasable."\
  "There are 2 ground level entry points to the castle, the main gate and the hidden entrance, both are marked on the map."\
  ""\
  "<h1>MISSION</h1>"\
  "Secure and deactivate the nuclear device (located in the castle church) within 35 minutes."\
  ""\
  "<h1>SERVICE/SUPPORT</h1>"\
  "3 MH-6M helicopters for transportation"\
  "2 AH-6M, both equipped with cameras and two M134, one also with a GAU-19 and 70mm rockets"\
  "Recommendation is to initially man all 3 MH-6M and 1 AH-6M, then after insertion double-man both AH-6M"\
  "Transport and CAS are coordinated by the designated FAC"\
  "The recon team has a small ISR drone"\
  ""\
  "<h1>COMSIG</h1>"\
  "0 (HQ), 1 (Assault), 2 (Assault), 3 (Support), 4 (Recon), 5 (Star)"\
  "Star callsigns: 51 52 53 for MH-6M, 54 55 for AH-6M"\
  "Recon team has a radio backpack for long range comms"\
  "48.0MHz, Air net 49.0MHz"
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "RHS_USAF"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 brief_extr {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Briefing"
  m_sTextData "<h1>SITUATION</h1>"\
  "A couple of hours ago, your extremist group (from a neighboring country of Bystrany) took control of Pasastejn castle."\
  "You are about to sacrifice your life, but it's all for a good cause: Your deep ethnic hatred of the Bystranian nation and its people."\
  "The plan is to detonate a low yield nuclear device, destroying the \"historic\" castle and killing thousands of Bystranian \"nationals\"."\
  "To enable the escape and survival of some important group members, the bomb has been put on a 35 minute countdown."\
  "You will protect the bomb until its detonation - your passionate hatred of Bystrany is already burning as hot as that second sun."\
  ""\
  "<b>a. Enemy Forces</b>"\
  "Unknown, possibly a counter terrorism unit, perhaps also foreign. Some enemies might even already be in the area, there is no way to know."\
  "You also have taken a couple of civilians hostage that were present at the castle. While you may wish to, do not yet harm them - they could serve as important human shields in the case of an attack."\
  ""\
  "<b>b. Friendly Forces</b>"\
  "Multiple small teams: HQ is at the northern tower, team 1 at the church which houses the bomb, team 2 at the main gate, team 3 at the south tower, the mortar team in the upper courtyard."\
  "One of the teams could be sent outside of the castle to conduct reconnaissance or unexpected ambushes."\
  ""\
  "<h1>MISSION</h1>"\
  "Protect the nuclear device at all cost, until it detonates in 35 minutes."\
  ""\
  "<h1>SERVICE/SUPPORT</h1>"\
  "3 night vision tubes (on the ground next to HQ and teams 1+2)"\
  "Multiple cars by the main gate"\
  "One 2B14 mortar in the upper courtyard, enough rounds to fire until sunrise"\
  ""\
  "<h1>COMSIG</h1>"\
  "0 (HQ), 1, 2, 3, 4 (mortar)"\
  "TLs have radios"
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "GC_SEPARATIST"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
 brief_drones {
  coords 3469.865 283.156 9234.433
  m_sTitle "Drone usage"
  m_sTextData "1. Place the drone in a spot suitable for takeoff"\
  "2. Take the drone controller from your backpack into your hands"\
  "3. Look at the drone and connect it to your controller"\
  "4. Once ready, equip the FPV goggles found in your backpack"\
  "5. When in first person view, press R to enable the rotors"\
  "6. If you want to leave first person view, press TAB to open your inventory and remove the FPV goggles"\
  ""\
  "<b>Controls:</b>"\
  "- Flight controls are mostly similar to helicopters"\
  "- Camera can be raised/lowered using up/down arrow keys"\
  "- Camera zoom can be adjusted using numpad +/-"\
  "- More info can be found in your controls menu"
  m_aVisibleForFactions {
   "RHS_USAF"
  }
  m_iOrder 1
 }
}